From: conda-forge
Subject: [PATCH] Disable ghcThreaded on Windows in Hadrian default flavour

On Windows, building GHC with -threaded causes "builderMainLoop: invalid argument"
errors when Stage 0 GHC spawns processes to build Stage 1/2. This is due to a bug
in process-1.6.16.0 (bundled with GHC 9.2.8) related to Windows job objects.

This patch modifies Hadrian's default flavour to set ghcThreaded=False on Windows,
which prevents the -threaded flag from being passed to ghc.exe builds on Windows.

See:
- https://hackage.haskell.org/package/process-1.6.24.0/changelog (fix in 1.6.18.0)
- https://github.com/haskell/cabal/issues/7309

diff --git a/hadrian/src/Settings/Default.hs b/hadrian/src/Settings/Default.hs
--- a/hadrian/src/Settings/Default.hs
+++ b/hadrian/src/Settings/Default.hs
@@ -218,7 +218,10 @@ defaultFlavour = Flavour
     , ghciWithDebugger   = False
     , ghcProfiled        = False
     , ghcDebugged        = False
-    , ghcThreaded        = True
+    -- CONDA-FORGE: Disable -threaded on Windows to avoid builderMainLoop errors
+    -- caused by process-1.6.16.0 job object bug (fixed in 1.6.18.0).
+    -- GHC 9.2.8 bundles process-1.6.16.0, so we disable threading on Windows.
+    , ghcThreaded        = not windowsHost
     , ghcDocs            = cmdDocsArgs }

 -- | Default logic for determining whether to build
